rComments: REALLY REALLY REALLY EASY A+. Just review your notebook once and do one or two pass exam before each test and you will get a really high score because the test are basically identical to the pass exam. Super easy, and give a lot of extra credit.

There is weekly online homework on Lon-Capa that is pretty straightforward. Lots of extra credit available. Highly suggest filling out the incomplete lecture notes because it is very similar to exam questions. Go over past exam in the notebook and you will be set for all exams. Highly suggest taking STAT 100 with her. Sidenote: She is pretty cute.

Karle is amazing! She's a really good lecturer who makes concepts easy to understand. She's very enthusiastic and helpful with the everyday office hours with her TAs. There're a LOT of extra credit opportunities to boost up your grade online with pre-lectures and the completed notebook. If you need to take STATS 100, definitely pick her class!
Exams are easy as long as you can memorize formulas and apply them to different scenarios. Lots of online homework
Exams are easy as long as you can memorize formulas and apply them to different scenarios. Karle is hilarious and you should definitely take her if you need to fulfill that Stat100 requirement!

She AWESOME!!! She makes statistics interesting. I know that stat 100 is known for easy A course, but I think it is easy because Laska is teaching. She is really good lecturer. Nice person, nice lecturer. GO FOR THIS CLASS!
Nicest teacher I've ever had

My favorite teacher ever. Assignments can be tedious, but it really helps you learn for the exams. She's really enthusiastic and is always available during her office hours. Lots of extra credit opportunities as long as you go to class. Easy A as long as you attend class!
Nice person but she assigns a lot of hw.
Amazing professor

Her attitude is so positive and bright every class. She explains the concepts veryyyyy precisely and clear. The class was an easy A and still offers a ton of extra credit. The incompleted class notes are veryyy helpful and make taking notes really easy.
STAT 100 is really easy, and that's probably only because of Professor Laska. She gives tons of extra credit and is incredibly sweet
Super nice, especially for such a big class. Hard to not get an A.

If there is any professor to take STAT 100 with, it's her. She's seriously amazing. If only all professors were as understanding and helpful as her. She gives extra credit, gives clear directions, takes great notes, and does not try to trick you on homework or the exams. Best class I've ever taken by far.
Go to class to get bonus points. She offers so much extra credit. There is a good amount of homework but it is easy. Easy class overall.

Karle is incredibly nice and is engaging to listen to. She is one of the nicest teachers I've had and is always available to her students and makes sure we understand the material. The course packet has practice exams, and TA Rachel gave reviews of previous exams which were really helpful. These reviews are optional but she gives good hints too.

Karle Laska is my favorite professor at U of I. She is very clear and concise and is always thorough in her teaching. She offers an insane amount of extra credit and iClicker points. I hate math, but she made me want to pursue Stats 200 next semester just because she made 100 so enjoyable for me.
This teacher is the best!

Karle is amazing! Even if you're not a math person you can do well in this class. I've found that stats is actually very useful in real life. You do have to do weekly homework and go to lectures to understand what's going on, but I promise Karle makes Stats great. Definitely not hard to get an A.
Easy class don't need the book unless you want to fill it out for extra credit. But it does help explain stuff if you don't go to lecture. Homework is on Lon capa and there's 3 midterms and a final.
